{
  "texts": [
    "Toward these ends and based on the results described in Sect. 3.2, a classifier (designated as classifier Alpha) was designed to represent an ideal model for our application.",
    "This classifier was fine-tuned by using the training data set augmented with 100 synthetic data and the number of epochs was fixed at 15.",
    "For comparison purposes, another classifier (designated as classifier Gamma) was also fine-tuned by using the same augmented dataset but with the number of epochs set to 40.",
    "Both classifiers were used to predict the stability of 1 million unlabeled candidate mixtures (collectively labeled the NADES/DES Universe) which were randomly generated by the uACL software.",
    "It is important to state that those mixtures present in the NADES/DES Universe were randomly generated, rather than fixing their constituents to a specific component such as ibuprofen or any other chemical."
  ]
}